-- Farmers in Russia’s Southern Rostov Start Planting Spring Crops
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-04-04T11:51:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/farmers-in-russia-s-southern-rostov-start-planting-spring-crops.html
Farmers in  Russia ’s southern Rostov
region started planting spring crops, with 1,500 hectares (3,706
acres) sown out of 2.2 million hectares expected, the region’s
agriculture ministry said.  Barley, peas and flax have been planted, the ministry said
in an e-mailed statement today. Of the 2.2 million hectares
expected, 1.1 million hectares will be oilseeds and the rest
grains and legumes, it said, citing Vyacheslav Vasilenko, deputy
governor of the ministry. Some 90 percent of winter crops are in
good and satisfactory condition in Rostov region, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
